Indeed, Tarantino consistently uses modern classic genre in telling his stories

00:00:35.960 --> 00:00:39.175
including western, spaghetti western, neo noir

00:00:39.180 --> 00:00:44.740
dark comedy, action, martial art, crime and horror

00:00:44.980 --> 00:00:50.160
Often, He concocts them in one film, then colors them with his own style, creating a genre of his own

00:00:51.220 --> 00:00:56.800
which was first manifested in his debut, Reservoir Dogs in 1992

00:00:57.540 --> 00:01:00.580
when he was 28 years old.

00:01:00.585 --> 00:01:03.315
 

00:01:03.460 --> 00:01:04.460
 

00:01:06.340 --> 00:01:12.540
Reservoir Dogs was not merely a heist movie, but rather a new cinematic phenomenon

00:01:12.760 --> 00:01:15.900
The Tarantino phenomenon, which relied on nonlinear storytelling

00:01:16.320 --> 00:01:19.180
fast-paced firey dialogue

00:01:19.185 --> 00:01:22.235
stylized violence colored with humor

00:01:22.240 --> 00:01:27.480
and pop culture references and music scores from the 60s and 70’s songs.

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:36.420
But the film that catapulted Tarantino to the pinnacle of Hollywood’s power and international fame was Pulp Fiction

00:01:36.980 --> 00:01:39.900
which was directed in 1994

00:01:40.960 --> 00:01:42.320
Pulp Fiction is a crime film

00:01:42.320 --> 00:01:45.675
in which Tarantino demolished mainstream cinema rules

00:01:45.680 --> 00:01:52.840
by using his cinematic style and nonlinear narrative in telling overlapping stories of gangsters

00:01:53.120 --> 00:01:55.300
and small-time criminals

00:01:55.480 --> 00:01:58.760
The film was an enormous commercial and critical success

00:01:59.000 --> 00:02:05.560
It snatched Cannes’ Palm D’or, followed by 7 Oscar nomination and one win

00:02:05.960 --> 00:02:12.320
It’s widely considered one of the greatest films ever, has been a source of inspiration to subsequent movies.

00:02:13.560 --> 00:02:15.760
